translations.gemini:
The good (sāttvikāḥ) sacrifice to the gods; 
 the passionate (rājasāḥ) to the Yakshas and Rakshasas; 
 And others sacrifice to the spirits of the dead (pretān) and the multitudes of ghosts (bhūta), 
 the people of darkness (tāmasāḥ).

translations.stoller_miller:
Men of lucidity sacrifice to the gods;
men of passion, to spirits and demons;
the others, men of dark inertia,
sacrifice to corpses and to ghosts.
